verses.text_plain: The Lord hear thee in the day of trouble; the name of the God of Jacob defend thee;
verses.verse_html:
1The Lord hear thee in the day of trouble; the name of the God of Jacob defend thee; ▼
▼ defend…: Heb. set thee on an high place

footnotes.body_text: ▼ defend…: Heb. set thee on an high place
footnotes.body_html: ▼ defend…: Heb. set thee on an high place

verses.text_plain: Send thee help from the sanctuary, and strengthen thee out of Zion;
verses.verse_html:
2Send thee help from the sanctuary, and strengthen thee out of Zion; ▼
▼ thee help: Heb. thy help
 , ▼
▼ strengthen: Heb. support

footnotes.body_html: ▼ thee help: Heb. thy help

verses.text_plain: Remember all thy offerings, and accept thy burnt sacrifice; Selah.
verses.verse_html:
3Remember all thy offerings, and accept thy burnt sacrifice; Selah. ▼
▼ accept: Heb. turn to ashes: or, make fat

footnotes.body_text: ▼ accept: Heb. turn to ashes: or, make fat
footnotes.body_html: ▼ accept: Heb. turn to ashes: or, make fat

verses.text_plain: Grant thee according to thine own heart, and fulfil all thy counsel.
verses.verse_html: 4Grant thee according to thine own heart, and fulfil all thy counsel.

tokens.text: thee according to thine own heart

verses.text_plain: We will rejoice in thy salvation, and in the name of our God we will set up our banners: the Lord fulfil all thy petitions.
verses.verse_html: 5We will rejoice in thy salvation, and in the name of our God we will set up our banners: the Lord fulfil all thy petitions.

verses.text_plain: Now know I that the Lord saveth his anointed; he will hear him from his holy heaven with the saving strength of his right hand.
verses.verse_html:
6Now know I that the Lord saveth his anointed; he will hear him from his holy heaven with the saving strength of his right hand. ▼
▼ his holy…: Heb. the heaven of his holiness
 , ▼
▼ with…: Heb. by the strength of the salvation of

footnotes.body_text: ▼ his holy…: Heb. the heaven of his holiness
footnotes.body_html: ▼ his holy…: Heb. the heaven of his holiness

footnotes.body_text: ▼ with…: Heb. by the strength of the salvation of
footnotes.body_html: ▼ with…: Heb. by the strength of the salvation of

verses.text_plain: Some trust in chariots, and some in horses: but we will remember the name of the Lord our God.
verses.verse_html: 7Some trust in chariots, and some in horses: but we will remember the name of the Lord our God.

verses.text_plain: They are brought down and fallen: but we are risen, and stand upright.
verses.verse_html: 8They are brought down and fallen: but we are risen, and stand upright.

verses.text_plain: Save, Lord: let the king hear us when we call.
verses.verse_html: 9Save, Lord: let the king hear us when we call.
